						<summary>

						<p>Door-jambs of the Hanumān temple near the village.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Undated).</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary and worn out inscription is not clear. It belongs to 12th century A.D. Mentions the [Hundred] and Twenty <hi rend="italic">[mahājanas],</hi> Avadhūtadēva, Kriyāśakti and Vāmadēva-paṇḍita.</p>						

